{"title":"Spiked pit","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Spiked_pit","type":"markdown","data":"| ^ spiked pit [![Spiked pit.png](/images/0/08/Spiked_pit.png)](/wiki/File:Spiked_pit.png) |                                                          |\n| ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Generates                                                                                | level 5+, [Fort Ludios](/wiki/Fort_Ludios \"Fort Ludios\") |\n| Effect                                                                                   | Prevents movement, damage                                |\n\nThe **spiked pit** is a [trap](/wiki/Trap \"Trap\") which is similar to the regular [pit](/wiki/Pit \"Pit\"), but can deal more damage.\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Generation](#Generation)\n- [2 Effects](#Effects)\n- [3 Removal](#Removal)\n- [4 History](#History)\n- [5 Messages](#Messages)\n- [6 References](#References)\n\n## Generation\n\nThe treasury in [Fort Ludios](/wiki/Fort_Ludios \"Fort Ludios\") contains many spiked pits along with its land mines.\n\n## Effects\n\n- *Main article: [Pit § Effects](/wiki/Pit#Effects \"Pit\")*\n\nSpiked pits have the same effects as normal pits, but additionally deal 1–10 damage. Each time you fall in, there is a 1⁄6 chance that the spikes will be poisoned, which can be fatal for a character without [poison resistance](/wiki/Poison_resistance \"Poison resistance\").[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1)\n\n[Metallivores](/wiki/Metallivore \"Metallivore\") can eat the spikes out of a spiked pit, turning it into a normal pit. [\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2)\n\nThe spikes are never poisoned when a monster falls in.[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3)\n\nPets that fall into a pit can be helped out by standing adjacent to the pit and untrapping in the direction of the pit. When you do this with a spiked pit, if you fail to remove your pet, they will suffer the effects of falling onto spikes each time you fail, making them angry (reducing their [tameness](/wiki/Tameness \"Tameness\")) and counting as abuse for resurrection from the [wand of undead turning](/wiki/Wand_of_undead_turning \"Wand of undead turning\"). If they die at your hands, you suffer the consequences of killing them in a trap yourself (−15 [alignment](/wiki/Alignment_record \"Alignment record\") and an [angry](/wiki/Anger \"Anger\") god).\n\n## Removal\n\nPush a [boulder](/wiki/Boulder \"Boulder\") into it, to create a regular floor tile. Alternatively, get a metallivore to eat the spikes to create a normal pit.\n\n## History\n\nSpiked pits were added in [NetHack 1.3d](/wiki/NetHack_1.3d \"NetHack 1.3d\").\n\n## Messages\n\n- You land on a set of sharp iron spikes.\n\n  You fell into a spiked pit instead of a normal pit.\n\n- \\<monster> munches on some spikes!\n\n  A metallivore ate the spikes in a spiked pit, creating a normal pit.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/trap.c in NetHack 3.6.6, line 1246](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.6_Released/src/trap.c#L1246)\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [src/trap.c in NetHack 3.6.6, line 2176](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.6_Released/src/trap.c#L2176)\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) [src/trap.c in NetHack 3.6.6, line 2445](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.6_Released/src/trap.c#L2445)\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.](/images/5/57/Nh366-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Spiked pit - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(f